metadata.name: L. Folk
metadata.description:
I knew you once. Your focus, and your heart. I held them briefly, but you grew in a way that became difficult for me to preserve, no matter how much I tried. 

I grew too. Perhaps why things became so heavy in the end. Perhaps why you let go. 

I still smell the sadness. Sporadic yet lingering. Not like overstayed cologne, but deeper, persistent, and unforgettable – like petrichor. 

No wonder it’s in the soil I tread, the bark I touch, the leaves I rub and the air I breathe. 

It’s in the bulbs I planted hoping the sweet scent of spring will be enough, this time, to guide me from your garden, into the meadow.
